INSERT INTO `faqs` (`id`, `contents`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1, '<h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 24px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: bold;">Frequently Asked Questions</span></font><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 24px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: bold;"><br></span></font></h1><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 24px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: bold;">Does NionTV contain any channels? Where can I get a playlist?</span></font></h1><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1;"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">No, NionTV application does not include any channels and no information will be provided about where you can get channels or channel packages. Also, application developers are not responsible for the content uploaded to NionTV.</span></font></h1><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1;"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><br></span></font></h1><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 24px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: bold;">My MAC address has changed after I switched to another connection type.</span></font></h1><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1;"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Each TV has 2 MAC addresses (1st is WiFi, 2nd is Ethernet) and a 2nd MAC is activated automatically after you switch to another connection type and restart the app. MAC address is unique for every TV and cannot be changed manually.</span></font></h1><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><br></h1><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 24px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: bold;">Why can''t I upload a playlist?</span></font></h1><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1;"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">NionTV only allows the legal providers who have licensed the copyright to upload the playlist, only then will we allow the upload for your DNS.</span></font></h1><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1;"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 24px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><br></span></font></h1><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 24px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: bold;">I get "Server (URL) connection timeout", "Check playlist URL" or "No playlist uploaded" messages, when starting the app, while my playlist URL that works on my computer, other devices and apps.</span></font></h1><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1;"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 24px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 18px;">Try example test list </span><a href="https://niontv.app/lists/example.m3u" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: 18px;">https://niontv.app/lists/example.m3u</span></a><span style="font-size: 18px;"> (external URL) first, then then check your playlist for errors. Make sure your URL is a direct link, not a redirect and that it is currently online. You can also try downloading your playlist file by putting the playlist URL in the internet browser address field and use it as a static playlist at </span><a href="https://niontv.app/device/playlists" target="_blank" style="font-weight: bold;"><span style="font-size: 18px;">My list</span></a><span style="font-size: 18px;"> page.</span></span></font></h1><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1;"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 24px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><br></span></font></h1><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1;"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">In case of Check playlist URL you can try turning off your TV/device from power cord for ~1 minute to clear device cache. Also try long pressing "0" or "CH", or long mouse click "Reload" button to force reload of playlist URL (disable app cache).</span></font></h1><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1;"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 24px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><br></span></font></h1><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1;"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Additionally, try reducing your playlist size by removing channels/movies (especially if you have LM series LG TV with limited memory). If your playlist doesn''t appear on TV or disappears after restart, try checking Save online box, when uploading the playlist. You can also try resetting Smart HUB or turn your TV off and on to clear the TV cache if you have Samsung TV.</span></font></h1><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1;"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 24px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><br></span></font></h1><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1;"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">TVs have limited memory available for app storage, so if your playlist is too big (~5 Mb), it might fail to save in TV''s memory.</span></font></h1><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1;"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><br></span></font></h1><h1 style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 1;"><span style="font-size: 24px;">For other questions, you can write to us on our mail&nbsp;</span><img style="width: 183.444px; float: none; height: 38.8646px;" data-filename="nionapp_support.JPG" src="/upload/16306250110.png" class=""><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><br></span></font></h1></h1>\n', '2020-04-03 20:33:09', '2021-09-02 20:24:42');
INSERT INTO `instructions` (`id`, `tag_id`, `contents`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(11, 0, '<p><a href="http://devsapp.u2u.co/instruction/samsung" target="_blank">How to install Samsung</a><br></p>\n', '2020-04-04 05:40:46', '2021-05-12 01:10:07'),
(12, 1, '<p class="MsoTitle"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);">INTRODUCTION FOR SAMSUNG TIZEN</span><p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:normal;mso-outline-level:3"><b><span style=''font-size: 24px; font-family: "Times New Roman", serif; color: rgb(196, 37, 87);''>How to load you own list to our application</span></b></p><p></p><p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:7.5pt;\r\nmargin-left:0cm;line-height:normal"><span style=''font-size: 13pt; font-family: "Times New Roman", serif;''>You can upload your own IPTV playlist by using mylist.</span></p><p></p><p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:normal;mso-outline-level:3"><b><span style=''font-size: 24px; font-family: "Times New Roman", serif; color: rgb(196, 37, 87);''>How to use the remote controller of Samsung\r\nTV`s</span></b></p><p></p><p></p><ul type="disc">\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal;"><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n     "Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>P+/P- and Arrows - switch channels<p></p></span></li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal;"><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n     "Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>UP - for select a categorie\r\n     or switching channels<p></p></span></li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal;"><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n     "Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>DOWN - for select a\r\n     categorie or switching channels<p></p></span></li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal;"><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n     "Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>Press (OK) while streaming\r\n     live Channel - show channel INFO bar<p></p></span></li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal;"><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n     "Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>SELECT (OK), - load channel\r\n     list in play mode<p></p></span></li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal;"><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n     "Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>RETURN - hide channel list\r\n     and infobar; Go back to channel list or home<p></p></span></li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal;"><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n     "Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>PLAY/PAUSE/STOP - play/pause/stop\r\n     stream/video (exit video player)<p></p></span></li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal;"><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n     "Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>EXIT - exit the application<p></p></span></li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal;"><b><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n     "Times New Roman";color:red;mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>RED</span></b><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n     "Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>&nbsp;- settings in primary\r\n     list; select audio/HLS track in stream/video<p></p></span></li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal;"><b><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n     "Times New Roman";color:orange;mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>YELLOW</span></b><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n     "Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>&nbsp;- adding to favorite\r\n     in primary list; adding to favorite in series and movies. <p></p></span></li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal;"><b><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n     "Times New Roman";color:blue;mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>BLUE -&nbsp;</span></b><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n     "Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>switching from\r\n     primary list to movies and series</span></li>\r\n</ul><h3><span style="color:#C42557"><span style="font-size: 24px;"><b>How to change the audio track</b></span><p></p></span></h3><p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:normal"><span style=''font-size: 13.5pt; font-family: "Times New Roman", serif;''>While streaming a movie or a serie you can change the language with red\r\nbutton; </span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:normal"><span style=''font-size: 13.5pt; font-family: "Times New Roman", serif;''>It will show you a menu where you can find Audio Language. In this sectio\r\nyou can switch between the languages.</span></p><p></p><p></p><h3><span style="color:#C42557"><b>How to change subtitels:</b><p></p></span></h3><p class="MsoNormal"><span style=''font-size:13.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\r\n"Times New Roman",serif''>While watching a movie you can use red key for adding\r\nsubtitel or removing.</span></p><p></p><p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style=''font-size:13.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\r\n"Times New Roman",serif''></span></p><p><br></p><p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:normal"><span style=''font-size: 13.5pt; font-family: "Times New Roman", serif;''></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:normal"><span style=''font-size: 13.5pt; font-family: "Times New Roman", serif;''></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class="MsoNormal"></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></p>\n', '2020-04-06 19:24:24', '2020-06-11 06:03:36'),
(13, 4, '<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:normal;mso-outline-level:3"><b><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;\r\nfont-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";\r\ncolor:#C42557;mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>Installing the app on Android TV\r\ndevices</span></b><p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:normal;mso-outline-level:3"><b><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;\r\nfont-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";\r\ncolor:#C42557;mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>Download link : http://iboplayer.com/tv.apk</span></b><span style=''font-family: "Times New Roman"; font-size: 17px;''>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; or&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;http://iboplayer.com/stb.apk</span></p><p></p><h3><span style=''font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;color:#C42557''>Loading your own\r\nplaylist<p></p></span></h3><p style="margin: 7.5pt 0cm;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">The application&nbsp;<strong>does not include any channels</strong>,\r\nit is only a tool to watch your <a href="https://iboiptv.com/device/login" target="_blank">IPTV</a> streams.</span></p><p></p><p style="margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:7.5pt;margin-left:\r\n0cm"><span style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Our\r\napp does not contains any channels, which mean that is only a Player for your IPTV\r\nlist. <br>\r\nYou need a Playlist to use our app!! We dont give any Playlist or information\r\nabout where you can find some. </span></p><p></p><p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:normal;mso-outline-level:3"><b><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;\r\nfont-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";\r\ncolor:#C42557;mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>How to install the app on Android TV\r\ndevices:</span></b></p><p></p><p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style=''font-family:"Arial",sans-serif''>IBO</span><span style=''font-family:"Arial",sans-serif''> PLAYER is Avaible on Google playstore. You can download and install the via Google playstore on devices which is supported. &nbsp;If you dont have the Playstore on you devices,\r\nthen is your TV not Android, which means that you cannot use the APP on this Device</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><iframe frameborder="0" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/UspMET2iPmI" width="640" height="360" class="note-video-clip"></iframe><br></p><p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:normal;mso-outline-level:3"><b><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;\r\nfont-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";\r\ncolor:#C42557;mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>How to install the app on Amazon Fire\r\nTV:</span></b></p><p></p><p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style=''font-family:"Arial",sans-serif''>You can\r\ndownload the app from Amazon Store and install it. When you dont see the app in\r\nAmazon Store you can use the Downloader for downloading our apk and installing.\r\nIn this case you have to change some settings from you Amazon stick. At first you\r\nhave to go in settings -&gt; my fire tv -&gt; Developer options -&gt; then you\r\nhave to enable the APPS from Unknow Sources. &nbsp;After do this you can install the APK.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style=''font-family:"Arial",sans-serif''>Download link :&nbsp; iboplayer.com/tv.apk</span><span style=''font-family: "Times New Roman"; font-size: 17px;''>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; or&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; iboplayer.com/stb.apk</span></p><p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:normal;mso-outline-level:3"><b><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;\r\nfont-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";\r\ncolor:#C42557;mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>Selecting a external Media Player:</span></b></p><p></p><p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style=''font-family:"Arial",sans-serif''>If you have ay\r\nproblem while streaming movie, series or channels you can select a external Player\r\nfrom settings. You can choose between VLC and MX player which is supported in\r\nour app. At first you have to download and install the external player from Google playstore. After that it would be activate in our app.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\r\nline-height:normal;mso-outline-level:3"><b><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;\r\nfont-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";\r\ncolor:#C42557;mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>How to use the Amazon Fire TV remote\r\ncontrole:</span></b></p><p></p><p></p><ul type="disc">\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal;"><b><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n     "Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>OK</span></b><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n     "Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>&nbsp;- show channel list;<p></p></span></li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal;"><b><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n     "Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>P+/P -</span></b><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n     "Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<b>Arrow\r\n     buttons</b>&nbsp;- navigate pages and channels<p></p></span></li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: normal;"><b><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n     "Times New Roman";mso-fareast-language:DE-AT''>UP -</span></b><span style=''font-size:13.5pt;font-family:"Arial",sans-serif;mso-fareast